CATD

CATD (Computer Aided Textile Design) is a sophisticated system that allows designers to create intricate patterns and designs for textiles using computer software. Our CATD solutions provide accuracy, speed, and flexibility, enabling you to bring your creative visions to life with ease.

Card Punching

Our card punching systems are designed to provide high precision and efficiency in punching patterns onto textile cards. This process is essential for the automation of looms and the creation of complex designs, ensuring consistent quality and reduced manual labor.

128 Hooks

Our 128 hooks system is designed for medium complexity patterns, offering a balance between design flexibility and operational simplicity. This system is perfect for small to medium scale textile operations looking to enhance their production capabilities.

256 Hooks

Our 256 hooks system offers increased complexity and versatility, enabling the creation of intricate patterns with high precision. This system is ideal for larger textile operations aiming to produce high-quality fabrics with detailed designs.

512 Hooks

Our 512 hooks system is designed for large-scale textile production, offering unmatched precision and speed. This system can handle highly complex patterns, making it suitable for producing premium quality fabrics with intricate designs.

768 Hooks

Our 768 hooks system is an advanced solution for complex textile designs, offering the highest level of precision and speed. This system is perfect for large-scale operations that demand the best in terms of quality and efficiency.

1024 Hooks

Our 1024 hooks system represents the pinnacle of textile design technology, capable of producing the most intricate and detailed patterns. This system is designed for the most demanding textile production environments, offering unparalleled performance and reliability.
